title: Printer's Sample Book, 1877
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small leatherbound notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used for printed textiles. Contains 143 samples in various patterns.
